      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for doing my homework here :)\n\nHow it\u0027s currently done in libpldm sees to be supported and also tested by GCC\n\nhttps://gcc.gnu.org/git/?p\u003dgcc.git;a\u003dblob;f\u003dgcc/testsuite/g%2B%2B.dg/ext/visibility/visibility-2.C;h\u003d26272abb1f9026fff55841ce5f3d8bdacb8d10d8;hb\u003d5115c7e447fc07457443df874bf57840e8316d5f\n\nhttps://gcc.gnu.org/git/?p\u003dgcc.git;a\u003dblob;f\u003dgcc/testsuite/g%2B%2B.dg/ext/visibility/visibility-5.C;h\u003d592529e665d6f65d323ed12060566e340639c255;hb\u003d5115c7e447fc07457443df874bf57840e8316d5f\n\nSo the behavior is unlikely to change in the future and we can continue to rely on it and avoid this huge diff.\n\nI will abandon this patch and upload new version of 87957.",
